  "title": "Senior/Quantity Surveyor (PUB/LTA Projects, North or East)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Study contract documents, take measurements, and prepare Bill of Quantities (BQ).</li>\n  <li>Assist with contract administration, progress claims, and liaise with Client’s representative on claims and variations.</li>\n  <li>Source quotations, compare pricing, and prepare BQ for tender pricing.</li>\n  <li>Prepare monthly budget statements for review by Superior.</li>\n  <li>Update Superior on all contractual and site matters.</li>\n  <li>Review and verify Subcontractor/Supplier claims, prepare payment certificates, and seek required approvals.</li>\n  <li>Attend site and progress claim meetings.</li>\n  <li>Monitor projects during the defect liability period after completion.</li>\n  <li>Maintain departmental Quality System.</li>\n  <li>Comply with WSH Act responsibilities to ensure workplace safety.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma and above in Engineering or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of working experience in construction industry.</li>\n  <li>Skilled in negotiation and problem-solving.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p>\n<p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p>\n<p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
